{
  "id": "indus_cisi_anchored_2",
  "name": "Indus CISI: Anchored Decipherment — 2 Anchor Readings (P385=n, P324=k)",
  "description": "First anchored decipherment attempt on real CISI inscription data. Anchors derived from structural analysis: P385 (T=0.83, preceded by P122 in 83% of cases) → 'n' (Dravidian genitive suffix -in phoneme /n/); P324 (I=0.78, most frequent initial sign n=99) → 'k' (Dravidian initial consonant /k/, as in 'ko' king/chief, 'kal' stone). These are the most structurally motivated readings. The SA must satisfy: P122→P385 bigram maps to a Dravidian genitive construction; P324 maps to a high-frequency Dravidian initial consonant. GPU: ocp_weight=0.0, n_seeds=5, max_iter=10000.",
